label.value: Gastric Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the submucosa. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the muscularis propria. A tumor may penetrate the muscularis propria with extension into the gastrocolic or gastrohepatic ligaments, or into the greater or lesser omentum, without perforation of the visceral peritoneum covering these structures. In this case, the tumor is classified as T3. If there is perforation of the visceral peritoneum covering the gastric ligaments or the omentum, the tumor should be classified as T4. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor penetrating the subserosal connective tissue without invasion of the visceral peritoneum or adjacent structures. The adjacent structures of the stomach include the spleen, transverse colon, liver, diaphragm, pancreas, abdominal wall, adrenal gland, kidney, small intestine, and retroperitoneum. Intramural extension to the duodenum or esophagus is not considered invasion of an adjacent structure, but is classified using the depth of the greatest invasion in any of these sites. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the serosa (visceral peritoneum) or adjacent structures. The adjacent structures of the stomach include the spleen, transverse colon, liver, diaphragm, pancreas, abdominal wall, adrenal gland, kidney, small intestine, and retroperitoneum. Intramural extension to the duodenum or esophagus is not considered invasion of an adjacent structure, but is classified using the depth of the greatest invasion in any of these sites. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the serosa (visceral peritoneum). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading adjacent structures/organs. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer in which the regional lymph node(s) cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Cardiopulmonary

value.value: Pertaining to both the heart and the lungs.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in one or two regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in three to six regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in seven or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in seven to fifteen regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in sixteen or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Fail Safe did not Operate

label.value: Unintended Compatibility Problem

label.value: Clinical Stage 0 Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ: intraepithelial tumor without invasion of the lamina propria, high grade dysplasia. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Clinical Stage I Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: (T1, N0, M0); (T2, N0, M0). T1: Tumor invades the lamina propria, muscularis mucosae, or submucosa. T2: Tumor invades the muscularis propria. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Clinical Stage II Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA: (T1, N1, N2, or N3, M0); (T2, N1, N2, or N3, M0); IIB: (T3, N0, M0); (T4a, N0, M0). T1: Tumor invades the lamina propria, muscularis mucosae, or submucosa. T2: Tumor invades the muscularis propria. T3: Tumor penetrates the subserosal connective tissue without invasion of the visceral peritoneum or adjacent structures. T4a: Tumor invades the serosa (visceral peritoneum). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Tumor with metastasis in one or two regional lymph nodes. N2: Tumor with metastasis in three to six regional lymph nodes. N3: Tumor with metastasis in seven or more regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Spindle Pole Body

value.value: The spindle pole body (SPB) is the microtubule organizing center (MTOC) in the yeast Saccharomyces that plays a pivotal role in such diverse processes as mitosis, budding, and mating. (from Cell. 1997;89:1077-86)

label.value: Clinical Stage III Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: (T3, N1, N2, or N3, M0); (T4a, N1, N2, or N3, M0). T3: Tumor penetrates the subserosal connective tissue without invasion of the visceral peritoneum or adjacent structures. T4a: Tumor invades the serosa (visceral peritoneum). N1: Tumor with metastasis in one or two regional lymph nodes. N2: Tumor with metastasis in three to six regional lymph nodes. N3: Tumor with metastasis in seven or more regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Clinical Stage IV Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: (T4b, Any N, M0); IVB: (Any T, Any N, M1). T4b: Tumor invades adjacent structures/organs. M0: No distant metastasis. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Clinical Stage IVA Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVA includes: (T4b, Any N, M0): T4b: Tumor invades adjacent structures/organs. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Clinical Stage IVB Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IVB includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Pathologic Stage 0 Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ: intraepithelial tumor without invasion of the lamina propria, high grade dysplasia. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Pathologic Stage I Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: IA: (T1, N0, M0); IB: (T1, N1, M0); (T2, N0, M0). T1: Tumor invades the lamina propria, muscularis mucosae, or submucosa. T2: Tumor invades the muscularis propria. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1: Tumor with metastasis in one or two regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Pathologic Stage IA Gastric Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IA includes: (T1, N0, M0). T1: Tumor invades the lamina propria, muscularis mucosae, or submucosa. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)
